Rating: 4
If you roast the sweet potatoes and the red peppers as well, this is truly a spectacular dish. I used probably 5lbs of potatoes for a large party, roasted them in the oven for until tender (1 hr), halfway through I tossed with the dressing. When finished, I refrigerated overnight. The next morning I roasted red peppers on the grill ( I recommend using more peppers and scallions than the recipe calls for). Made another batch of dressing, added the roasted peppers and the scallions and refrigerated for 4 hours. Tossed the potatoes with the dressing just before serving and everyone ooh-ed and aah-ed!

