Rating: 4
I couldn't resist the temptation to roast the sweet potatoes. This way they wouldn't be as fragile and would have a more complex not so sweet flavor. I cut them in 1" disks then cut the disks in fourths to speed up the cubing process. I tossed them in a plastic bag with olive oil, dumped them into a roasting pan with salt & cracked pepper and roasted them for 1 hour at 375°. After that I followed the recipe. This is a definite keeper! It looks beautiful and it tastes soooo good. After sitting 15 minutes I thought it was perfect after that it absorbed all of the dressing and it was still good and the next day it's good enough to sneak from the fridge (I just checked.)

